  <brief_title>Seroquel in Acute Mania: Study to Investigate if Valproate Add-On Therapy is Superior to Quetiapine Monotherapy in Acutely Manic Patients</brief_title>
  <official_title>Phase IV Study to Investigate if Valproate Add-on Therapy is Superior to Quetiapine Monotherapy in Acutely Manic Patients</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>AstraZeneca</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>AstraZeneca</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary purpose is to investigate whether the addition of sodium valproate will be
      superior to treatment with quetiapine (Seroquel) given as monotherapy for an additional 14
      days in non-responding patients after a 14 day initial treatment period with quetiapine.

      PLEASE NOTE: Seroquel SR and Seroquel XR refer to the same formulation. The SR designation
      was changed to XR after consultation with FDA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
